    "navalog Vol 57No 6 MASTER DIVER BECOMES WARRANT SEW WARRANT OFFICER In ceremonies held nt the V S Naval Underwater Ordnance Station on the 81st of January Eugene E McNlff BMC of the stations diving crew Joined the Warrant Officer ranks of the Navy as a Boatswain Warrant McNlff is being sworn in by CAPT 11 Maynard Commanding Officer of the Underwater Ordnance Station 2Day Seminar Held to Study Pest Control Military and civilian represent atives of local naval activities met at the Naval Base here Wednesday and Thursday 30 and 31 January to attend a twoday sentin ir on the supervision and preventive measures of pest con trol Sponsored by the Commandant First Naval District the train ing course was under the direc tion of Dr John W H Rehn civilian entomoligist for the First and Third Naval District The course stressed the ini portance of sanitation chemical controls structural design and physical controls as preventative measures in controlling pests such as mosquitoes flies and vari ous rodents It also dealt with the duties of those personnel de signated Pest Control Supervis ors and Operators who handle the various pesticides now in use The course was the first of"
